text: January unemployment rates ranged from 2.2% in NE and UT to 5.9% in NM.
In Q4 2021, eight states saw their greatest annual house price growth in three decades.
GDP growth between Q3 2020 and Q3 2021 ranged from 0.2% in Alaska to 7.4% in Tennessee.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in January were below prepandemic levels in 46 states and DC.
Average private weekly earnings in January ranged from $825 in MS to $1,329 in MA.
State and local public jobs were below prepandemic levels in each state except ID and ND.
MN and 39 other states saw manufacturing GDP exceed prepandemic levels in Q3 2021.
Every state (but not DC) saw annual house price increases exceed 10% in Q4 2021.
In January 2022, 10 states saw their lowest unemployment rates in 45 years.
In Q3 2021, retail GDP was below prepandemic levels in every state except Washington.
